rComments: He is very intelligent, a very nice & every time available! It was a fantastic experience for me to take History of the Balkans with him. I am looking forward to taking other classes if he teaches other stuff...I strongly recommend him. Nevertheless, you have to be passionate about the topic plus work hard.

Very insightful prof. His English is fine, we understood him without any problems and he knows his subject very well. My only complaint was that we needed a text book or printed readings to follow for better course structure. I'm not sure if he has changed that now or not. Overall though it was an interesting class and a good grade is attainable.

His course is probably for people really interested in European History. He is not teaching for High School for sure! This guy is clever and passionate. He pushes you to have an intellectual basis, not only broad understanding. I read what he recommended. Then, listening to him I realized how biased I was. I fully recommend him. He’s different -)!

Very nice guy. Lectures are sometimes difficult to follow, but he is willing to help out as much as he can outside of class. He is extremely knowledgeable; very smart man! Midterm is easy if class is attended and readings are read. His English isn't that good, but he has a great sense of humor and wants first and foremost for his students to learn!

Easiest grade that I ever got.  Midterm and final were ridiculously easy if you knew what you were talking about.  His class was a mess, for sure, but as long as you dedicated yourself to learning the subject, you could excel in that class, no problem.

Marin = incompetence and mediocrity! His English is awful! He is reading from his notes, or talking on irrelevant topics. He starts sentences that never finishes! The students have to correct his blatant mistakes, such as "UN in 1934." We told him that in 1934, there was a League of Nations that had nothing to do with UN! I wonder who hired him?!
